(6, 'CAR-T Cell Therapy', 'CAR-T Cell Therapy', 'The unique treatment is a type of immunotherapy called engineered cell therapy or effector cell therapy.', '<p style=\"text-align: start; color: rgb(102, 102, 102); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-size: 15px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; line-height: 1.5;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">(CAR) stands for chimeric antigen receptor. CAR T cells therapy activates a person&apos;s immune system to fight cancer. The unique treatment is a type of </span><a href=\"https://canceronco.com/treatments/immunotherapy\" style=\"color: transparent;font-family: Poppins, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(41, 128, 185);\"><strong>immunotherapy&nbsp;</strong></span></a><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">called engineered cell therapy or effector cell therapy. Immunotherapy is still new but it works for adults and children for whom other treatments have stopped working.</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: start; color: rgb(102, 102, 102); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-size: 15px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; line-height: 1.5;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">The T cell is the central component of the immune system. In CAR T cell therapy, the doctor collects T cells from the patient&apos;s blood, then takes them to the laboratory and researches the T cells and tries to destroy any cells found to be effective against cancer.</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: start; color: rgb(102, 102, 102); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-size: 15px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; line-height: 1.5;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">The modified cells are then injected back into the patient&apos;s body. If the tes